# Hypothesis portfolio

Single source of truth for all hypotheses in this research project. Updated at the end of
every experiment notebook.

## Status legend

- `planned`: stated but no validation notebook yet
- `in-progress`: notebook running
- `supported`: validation met the acceptance condition
- `rejected`: validation met the rejection condition
- `partial`: only some conditions met (e.g. positive at fee 0 but negative at fee 1 bp)
- `parked`: blocked on upstream hypothesis or deferred to a later session
- `dropped`: judged not worth pursuing

## Entries

| ID | Statement | Status | Linked experiments | Acceptance condition | Last update |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| H1 | [Falsifiable comparison statement.] | planned | (none yet) | [numeric threshold] | YYYY-MM-DD |
| H2 | ... | ... | ... | ... | ... |

## Adding hypotheses

- IDs are sequential (H1, H2, ..., H10, H11, ...)
- Each statement is a falsifiable comparison statement (see `references/research_design.md`)
- Acceptance condition is a numeric threshold
- Derived hypotheses keep a reference to their parent (e.g. `H10 (derived from H3): ...`)

## Do not delete

Even rejected and dropped hypotheses stay in this file. They are needed to trace decisions
later. Just update the status.

## Derivation tree

Sketch derivation:

```
H1 (parent claim)              [supported]
├── H2 (variant)               [rejected]
├── H3 (alternative)           [partial]
│   ├── H10 (refinement)       [planned]
│   └── H11 (extension)        [parked: needs new data]
└── H4 (combination)           [planned]
```
